post_text:
Good Morning and Happy Friday!

As we approach Halloween, please be mindful of the rules while on KUSD School Campus.

General parking will be located at the Main High School and Elementary School parking lots from 5: 00 pm to 9:00pm.

We ask that you please comply with all traffic signs, detours and drive within the posted speed limit of 15 mph while on campus.

We have asked District Tenants to display a sign if they are out of candy or don't have candy. If porch lights are off, this is also a sign of no candy and please do not disturb the tenant.

Security will be on patrol throughout campus to ensure the safety of the public.

Thank you for in advance for your understanding and support.

Happy Halloween!!!

post_text:
Kayenta Unified School District No. 27 is pleased to inform you that all students attending: Kayenta Business Center (KBC), Kayenta Elementary School (KES), Kayenta Middle School (KMS) and Monument Valley High School (MVHS) will receive FREE breakfast and lunch starting April 1, 2016. KUSD is implementing a new option under the National School Lunch and School Breakfast Programs called the Community Eligibility Provision (CEP) for the remainder of the 2015-16 school year and for the next 3 school years.

Great news for you and your students! All enrolled students of KUSD are eligible to receive a healthy breakfast and lunch at school at no charge to your household. No further action is required of you and no more applications to complete. Your children will be able to participate in these meal programs without having to pay a fee or submit an application. This will be in effect through 2018-19 School Year, so no more applications to complete! If you have other questions or need help, call Arleen Blackwater at 928-697-2232.

post_text: Kayenta Unified School District invites your participation in a forum to discuss Student Clubs this Tuesday November 17th. We offer two different times and locations for KUSD staff and for community members. All participants are welcome at either location: school staff are encouraged to attend at the Nash Auditorium at 3:45 PM, and our school community is encouraged to attend at the Kayenta Township Town Hall at 5:15 PM. The forum will include a PowerPoint presentation by an attorney, followed by a Q&A Question and Answer session. Please set a reminder for this coming Tuesday, November 17th, for our conversation about student clubs! Thank you.

post_text: We are proud of our Lady Mustangs and wonderful coaches!
shared_text:
Navajo Times
November 9, 2014 at 1:57 AM ·

JUST IN

The State Champion Monument Valley Lady Mustangs get together for a photo with the trophy after beating Cactus 3 games to 1 Saturday night at the Prescott Valley Events Center. The Monument Valley Lady Mustangs captured their ninth state volleyball title. For more on the title game and the Volleyball State Championships, get your copy of the Navajo Times this coming Thursday for stories and photos. (Special to the Times - Matt Hinshaw)
